    full: "This question requires calculating depreciation and then the profit or loss on sale. The asset was bought on January 1, 1997 and sold on June 30, 2001. That is 4 years and 6 months (half a year). Annual depreciation is ₦60,000 × 10% = ₦6,000. For 4.5 years, total depreciation is ₦6,000 × 4.5 = ₦27,000. The Net Book Value (NBV) at the time of sale is Cost - Total Depreciation = ₦60,000 - ₦27,000 = ₦33,000. The asset was sold for ₦16,000. Since the sale price is less than the NBV, there is a loss. Loss = NBV - Sale Price = ₦33,000 - ₦16,000 = ₦17,000. This loss is recorded in the profit and loss account as an expense."
