    full: "To calculate straight line depreciation, you need three pieces of information: the original cost of the asset, the estimated scrap value (what you can sell it for at the end of its life), and the estimated useful life in years. The formula is: (Cost - Scrap Value) / Useful Life. In this example: Cost = ₦500,000, Scrap Value = ₦50,000, Useful Life = 10 years. So (₦500,000 - ₦50,000) = ₦450,000. Divide by 10 gives ₦45,000. This means each year for 10 years, you will record depreciation expense of ₦45,000. After 10 years, the net book value will be ₦500,000 - (10 × ₦45,000) = ₦500,000 - ₦450,000 = ₦50,000, which equals the scrap value."
