    e: "COGS = Opening stock ₦50,000 + Purchases ₦200,000 - Closing stock ₦40,000 = ₦210,000. Gross Profit = Sales ₦300,000 - COGS ₦210,000 = ₦90,000.",
    full: "This question requires both steps of the gross profit calculation. First, calculate Cost of Goods Sold (COGS): Opening Stock (₦50,000) + Purchases (₦200,000) = Goods Available for Sale (₦250,000). Then subtract Closing Stock (₦40,000) to get COGS = ₦210,000. This means the goods that were sold cost the business ₦210,000. Second, calculate Gross Profit: Sales (₦300,000) - COGS (₦210,000) = ₦90,000. This means the business made a gross profit of ₦90,000 from its buying and selling activities. The gross profit margin is 30% (₦90,000/₦300,000). This is a healthy margin in many industries. The business will now deduct its operating expenses from this gross profit to find the net profit. If operating expenses are, say, ₦50,000, the net profit would be ₦40,000."
