    full: "When a partner retires, the partnership may continue with the remaining partners. The retiring partner is entitled to their share of capital, goodwill, revaluation surplus, etc. The remaining partners may choose to purchase the retiring partner's share. The accounting entry is: Debit the retiring partner's capital account (to close it), Credit the remaining partners' capital accounts (in their gaining ratio - the ratio in which they will share the retiring partner's share of future profits). For example, if A retires and B and C will take over A's share equally, then B and C's capital accounts are each credited with half of A's capital balance. If the retiring partner is paid in cash, there is an additional entry: Debit the retiring partner's capital account (further reducing it to zero), Credit Bank (paying the amount due). If the retiring partner is not paid immediately, the amount due may be shown as a loan or payable in the balance sheet. The new profit-sharing ratio among the remaining partners must be determined and disclosed."
